      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Concept ACK.  Regarding the lint failure about not quoting the new variable, I am unsure whether this lint failure is actually a problem.  It seems to me that some users may wish to pass extra arguments to whatever executable is used in place of `gpg`; quoting the variable would prevent this use case.  Thoughts?",
